  "time_ut": 1658490824,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2019\u2019\u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0db8\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dd2 \u0d8b\u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dbb \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf\u2019\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Vihara Maha Devi Park will be reserved for the activists.",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Chief organizer of the opposition MP Lakshman Kiriella said in Colombo today (22) that he regrets the way the president is acting when he announced at the party leader's meeting that Vihara Maha Devi Park will be reserved for the activists.",
        "Mr. Kiriella said that the attack on the activists, lawyers and media persons has caused a lot of damage to the country's image, despite the fact that the activists have declared that they will leave within 24 hours.",
        "Mr. Lakshman Kiriella, the main organization of the opposition, who further commented at a press conference held in Colombo, also said:",
        "\"The whole world was watching this peaceful struggle. And they had announced that within 24 hours this struggle would be temporarily stopped. Despite this, we cannot accept this attack at all. The new president told us in the recent party leader meeting that Vihara Maha Devi Park will be reserved for the strugglers. He said clearly. Attacking innocent activists, lawyers, journalists and international journalists while we have declared that we will withdraw within 24 hours is a big damage to our image. At a time when our country is bankrupt, especially when we are asking for help from the rest of the world, this kind of attack is putting Sri Lanka in a frying pan. States like the European Union, Great Britain, America, and Canada have already strongly condemned this attack. A plan against our country has already been passed before the International Human Rights Council. It is very clear that what is happening is that this government is following the same path as the previous government."
      ],
